BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF HAWAII:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 286, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
2 amended by adding two new sections to be appropriately
3 designated and to read as follows:
4 "§286- License plate flipping devices; prohibited. (a)
5 No person shall operate a motor vehicle with, possess, purchase,
6 install, sell, offer for sale, or otherwise distribute a license
7 plate flipping device. This section shall apply to any motor
8 vehicle operated on public roadways in the State, regardless of
9 the jurisdiction of registration. Each act described in this
10 subsection shall constitute a separate and distinct violation,
11 regardless of whether multiple acts occur simultaneously or are
12 committed in connection with other violations.
13 (b) Notwithstanding any other provisions of this chapter,
14 any person who violates this section shall be fined no less than
15 $750 but no more than $1,000 for each separate violation. Each
16 instance of a violation shall constitute a separate offense.
